<section data-depth="1" id="fs-id2240187" class="free-response"><h3 data-type="title">Critical Thinking Questions</h3>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id2515816">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id2459510"><p id="fs-id2242080">Give the formula for net filtration pressure.</p></div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id2399648" data-label="">
<p id="fs-id1637897">Net filtration pressure (NFP) = glomerular blood hydrostatic pressure (GBHP) &#8211; [capsular hydrostatic pressure (CHP) + blood colloid osmotic pressure (BCOP)]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id2016531">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id2353210"><p id="fs-id2743599">Name at least five symptoms of kidney failure.</p></div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1483809" data-label="">
<p id="fs-id2568467">Symptoms of kidney failure are weakness, lethargy, shortness of breath, widespread edema, anemia, metabolic acidosis or alkalosis, heart arrhythmias, uremia, loss of appetite, fatigue, excessive urination, and oliguria.</p>
</div>
</div>
