<div data-type="glossary"><h3 data-type="glossary-title">Glossary</h3>
<dl id="fs-id1424734"><dt>glomerular filtration rate (GFR)</dt> <dd id="fs-id2637990">rate of renal filtration</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id2853934"><dt>inulin</dt> <dd id="fs-id1989679">plant polysaccharide injected to determine GFR; is neither secreted nor absorbed by the kidney, so its appearance in the urine is directly proportional to its filtration rate</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id2265636"><dt>net filtration pressure (NFP)</dt> <dd id="fs-id2403316"> pressure of fluid across the glomerulus; calculated by taking the hydrostatic pressure of the capillary and subtracting the colloid osmotic pressure of the blood and the hydrostatic pressure of Bowman&#8217;s capsule</dd></dl>
<dl id="fs-id2124455"><dt>systemic edema</dt> <dd id="fs-id1639120">increased fluid retention in the interstitial spaces and cells of the body; can be seen as swelling over large areas of the body, particularly the lower extremities</dd></dl>
